duties_responsibilities.duty: Handle a variety of health-related problems and lead a multi-disciplinary care team supporting patients' physical, emotional, and social wellness.
Provide senior-focused primary care for members of Medicare Advantage health plans and manage chronic and acute-care conditions.
Deliver health education and value-added, well-being services to patients and community members to improve their health.
Contribute to continuously improving consumer experiences and promoting lifelong well-being for associates and the communities served.

education_certification.credential: Doctorate degree from an accredited MD or DO program of an accredited university. Board Certification or true board eligibility in Family Medicine or Internal Medicine.
